  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>You know how to use your momentum to enhance your thrown weapon attacks.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Point-Blank Shot.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>You can use the charge rules to make a thrown weapon attack. All the parameters of a charge apply, except that you must only move closer to your opponent, and you must end your movement within 30 feet of that opponent. If you do, you can make a single thrown weapon attack against that opponent, gaining the +2 bonus on the attack roll and taking a -2 penalty to your AC until the start of your next turn.<br/><br/><b>Combat Trick</b><br/>When using this feat, you can spend 2 stamina points to end your movement within 50 feet of your target instead of 30 feet.",
